Jdgs9:46 And when all the men of the tower of Shechem heard <em>that</em>, they entered into an hold of the house of the god Berith.
Jdgs9:47 And it was told Abimelech, that all the men of the tower of Shechem were gathered together.
Jdgs9:48 And Abimelech gat him up to mount Zalmon, he and all the people that <em>were</em> with him; and Abimelech took an axe in his hand, and cut down a bough from the trees, and took it, and laid <em>it</em> on his shoulder, and said unto the people that <em>were</em> with him, What ye have seen me do, make haste, <em>and</em> do as I <em>have done</em>.
Jdgs9:49 And all the people likewise cut down every man his bough, and followed Abimelech, and put <em>them</em> to the hold, and set the hold on fire upon them; so that all the men of the tower of Shechem died also, about a thousand men and women.
Jdgs9:50 Then went Abimelech to Thebez, and encamped against Thebez, and took it.
Jdgs9:51 But there was a strong tower within the city, and thither fled all the men and women, and all they of the city, and shut <em>it</em> to them, and gat them up to the top of the tower.
Jdgs9:52 And Abimelech came unto the tower, and fought against it, and went hard unto the door of the tower to burn it with fire.
Jdgs9:53 And a certain woman cast a piece of a millstone upon Abimelech's head, and all to brake his skull.
Jdgs9:54 Then he called hastily unto the young man his armourbearer, and said unto him, Draw thy sword, and slay me, that men say not of me, A woman slew him. And his young man thrust him through, and he died.
Jdgs9:55 And when the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, they departed every man unto his place.
Jdgs9:56 Thus God rendered the wickedness of Abimelech, which he did unto his father, in slaying his seventy brethren:
Jdgs9:57 And all the evil of the men of Shechem did God render upon their heads: and upon them came the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal.
Jdgs10:1 And after Abimelech there arose to defend Israel Tola the son of Puah, the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar; and he dwelt in Shamir in mount Ephraim.
Jdgs10:2 And he judged Israel twenty and three years, and died, and was buried in Shamir.
